* A FEW THINGS YOU MUST KNOW! READ CAREFULY!! *

    THE DEADLINE FOR ALL CATHEGORIES IS SUNDAY, JULY THE 26th, AT
12:00!!! (noon). after this time, we will not accept any entries
unless we are contacted previously with an explanation that it will
be late because of objective reasons. we are asking you to prepare
everything and bring it along on time, because this way you make
less problems for us AND yourself, since this way everything will
happen as scheduled, with no unnecessary delays! So, bring your
productions on SATURDAY, SATURDAY NIGHT or SUNDAY MORNING, on
sunday, after the deadline, we will accept only work that has been
completed on the party place!

    the AMIGA and PC cathegories will not be merged under any
condition. if there is only one entry per cathegory, it is
proclaimed winner and it gets a prize (if there is one for the
specific compo). this holds for all but the multichannel compo,
where all modules will compete together.

    the MUSIC CATHEGORIES, where there is always way too many
entries, will probably be preselected down to a decent number of
approx. 10 or so modules. this will allow for every tune to be
carefuly listened to and heard for 5 minutes, and will eliminate the
standard "avoiding the multichannels" syndrome. the jury will be
spontaneously selected on the party itself, and is most likely to
consist of one musician from Pas Maters, Hyperopia, Eastgate, Mad
Virgin and CoRRoSioN. No complaints about the work of the jury are
allowed.

    the 4CHANNEL compo is PROTRACKER ONLY! which means that ONLY
modules playable by a standard PROTRACKER 2.3b will be considered.
the module can be made on a PC, too, but must conform to this
condition.

    PC MULTICHANNEL entries can be in FASTRACKER(][) (XM, MOD),
IMPULSETRACKER(IT) or SCREAMTRACKER (S3M) format.

    the AMIGA MULTICHANNEL entries can be either in SOUNDSTUDIO (MMD3),
DIGIBOOSTER (DBM) or SYMPHONIE (SymMOD) format. This cathergory is
exempt from the general rule of not mixing Amiga and PC productions,
because there is no real reason for the separation, so all modules
compete equaly in the same cathegory.

    the GRAPHICS CATHEGORIES will be displayed from the appropriate
machines, with the author having the right to request a specific
platform. if it is not requested, the organisers will choose the
platform according to the pictures resolution and format. the same
goes for the ASCII compo. ANSI IS NOT ALLOWED!!!

    WILD COMPO entries are recommended to be brought along on VHS.
alternatively, you can use one of the compo machines as a player for
your animation in allowed formats (AVI, MPEG - PC and ANIM - AMIGA).
if your production uses a special player, you must deliver it
together with the entry. Also, if your production uses special
hardware (computer) which is not mentioned in this text, you are
obliged to bring it along, and you should notify the organisers
before SATURDAY NIGHT!

    this time the NAMES OF THE AUTHOR AND GROUP will be displayed
during all the compos, as well as during the voting. it is the
visitor's right to vote for whoever they want to, and it is their
right to support those few that truly try to deliver quality on the
scene or not. people we notice "helping" others vote will be removed
from the party place and most likely disqualified.

    the organisers reserve the right to kill the votes of those who
vote using the tickets of their aunts, moms, brothers, chicks, and
the likes (of course, if they are noticed doing this). let's just
say that everyone has the right to vote once, only.


PRIZES:

    considering that the biggest problem about organising a demo
party are the prizes, we are not able to deliver you an exact list
at the moment, nor can we positively claim how many or what will
they be, but we will give you a few informations, just to make
things clearer until the next version of the invitation comes out.

    first and foremost, the prizes will be adequate for the compos
they are given out for. so, there won't be any more books. ;-)

    second, the prizes will most likely be hardware. the winner of a
cathegory will receive a computer add-on (or an entire computer)
that is appropriate for their machine, accorging to the cathegory.
Amiga people will get things they can use on _their_ machines, and
the same goes for PC users.

    third, the minimum of prizes that will most certainly be handed
out encompasses the two main cathegories - AMIGA DEMO and PC DEMO.
the other compos will have prizes if we manage to get them.

    fourth, and perhaps most important, is, that the way things are
going at the moment, none of the prizes will be cheaper than 150
DEM. 

     more about the prizes, as well as a complete listing of them
will be released in the final invitation which should come out
a week before the party.


